"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1934507-Olympics-2024-Paris-weird-rules\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The2024 Paris Olympicsconsists of 32 sports, some of which are not often seen apart from the quadrennial global competition.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 126, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Paris Olympicsconsists\", \"from\": 8, \"to\": 30}, {\"ngram\": \"32 sports\", \"from\": 34, \"to\": 43}, {\"ngram\": \"the quadrennial global competition\", \"from\": 89, \"to\": 123}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With over 17,000 athletes taking part in the French capital across 16 days of action-packed events, hundreds of medals have already been handed out.\", \"from\": 128, \"to\": 276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 173, \"end\": 179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9561779177115195, \"rank\": 0.04080519533153439, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"over 17,000 athletes\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 153}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 165}, {\"ngram\": \"16 days\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 202}, {\"ngram\": \"action-packed events\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 226}, {\"ngram\": \"hundreds\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 236}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 240, \"to\": 246}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But not every athlete stays on the right side of the rules, with disqualifications and punishments common due to the strict rules in place in some events.\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 432, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every athlete\", \"from\": 286, \"to\": 299}, {\"ngram\": \"the right side\", \"from\": 309, \"to\": 323}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 327, \"to\": 336}, {\"ngram\": \"disqualifications\", \"from\": 343, \"to\": 360}, {\"ngram\": \"punishments\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 376}, {\"ngram\": \"the strict rules\", \"from\": 391, \"to\": 407}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 416}, {\"ngram\": \"some events\", \"from\": 420, \"to\": 431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Express Sport looks at 11 of the strangest and most bizarre rules at the Olympics, from cosmetic hygiene to staying completely silent during an event.\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 584, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Express Sport\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"the strangest and most bizarre rules\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 499}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"cosmetic hygiene\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 538}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 583}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You will not see a basketball player hanging from the hoop after completing a slam dunk at the Olympics, at least not legally.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 712, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a basketball player\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"the hoop\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 644}, {\"ngram\": \"a slam dunk\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 689}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rulebook prohibits players from holding onto the rim after shooting due to the injury risk involved or potential damage to the equipment.\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rulebook\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 726}, {\"ngram\": \"players\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 744}, {\"ngram\": \"the rim\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"the injury risk\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"potential damage\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 837}, {\"ngram\": \"the equipment\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 854}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, dunking is allowed - as we saw with Joel Embiid during the USA's victory over France on Friday.\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 901, \"end\": 912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Joel Embiid\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\"}, {\"begin\": 924, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 1.0588988144357596e-11, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 943, \"end\": 949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9884211529493885, \"rank\": 0.004708617076294566, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 959}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coin tosses are used in several sports such as football to make objective decisions.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Coin tosses\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 973}, {\"ngram\": \"several sports\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 1000}, {\"ngram\": \"football\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1017}, {\"ngram\": \"objective decisions\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beach volleyball is another where it is utilised, but only to determine which team should change their uniform if they turn up wearing the same colour.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1198, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Beach volleyball\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"which team\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"their uniform\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"the same colour\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1197}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When you are hopping on the bike, do not forget to tuck in your shirt.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1272, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the bike\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"your shirt\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1271}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Apparently BMX athletes are required to tuck in their clothing, even if it matches their bottoms, to prevent loose clothing from getting caught in the bike's machinery.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.547788908451852e-12, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their clothing\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"their bottoms\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1369}, {\"ngram\": \"loose clothing\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike's machinery\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's safe to say there may be more dangerous ways to get injured when participating in a BMX event than getting your clothes entangled, though.\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1532, \"end\": 1535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.547788908451852e-12, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more dangerous ways\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"your clothes\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competitors in the boxing event must be clean-shaven or have very limited facial hair.\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1674, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Competitors\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"the boxing event\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"very limited facial hair\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rule was implemented to ensure cuts and injuries are easily visible to determine whether a fight should be stopped or if medical attention is required.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1830, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rule\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"cuts\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1714}, {\"ngram\": \"injuries\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1727}, {\"ngram\": \"a fight\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"medical attention\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While a beard is not permitted, a pencil moustache is allowed.\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1894, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a beard\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1845}, {\"ngram\": \"a pencil moustache\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1882}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another fashion-based rule means that cyclists can only wear their socks midway up their calf and they are measured by Olympic officials.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 2035, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Another fashion-based rule\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1924}, {\"ngram\": \"cyclists\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"their socks\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 1970}, {\"ngram\": \"their calf\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1991}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic officials\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's because longer socks can provide an aerodynamic advantage by reducing drag, and regulating sock length ensures all cyclists compete under the same conditions.\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"longer socks\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2064}, {\"ngram\": \"an aerodynamic advantage\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"drag\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2118}, {\"ngram\": \"sock length\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2146}, {\"ngram\": \"all cyclists\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2167}, {\"ngram\": \"the same conditions\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2201}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's all about training and staying quiet in the equestrian event as a Swedish athlete found out at the 1932 Olympics.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2253, \"end\": 2263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9999999957822183, \"rank\": 4.218007219059894e-09, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}, {\"begin\": 2275, \"end\": 2282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"score\": 0.9990659392338568, \"rank\": 0.0009261299113895204, \"text\": \"Swedish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 2219, \"to\": 2227}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1932 Olympics\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2321}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They clicked their tongue, which was deemed as a way of guiding the horse.\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2397, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their tongue\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2348}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2375}, {\"ngram\": \"the horse\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2396}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And despite their protests, claiming it was due to the saddle, they were penalised.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their protests\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2424}, {\"ngram\": \"the saddle\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2459}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While gymnasts are allowed to wear colourful makeup to match their sparkling outfits, nail polish is not permitted.\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2600, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gymnasts\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2499}, {\"ngram\": \"colourful makeup\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2536}, {\"ngram\": \"their sparkling outfits\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"nail polish\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2582}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is a good reason for this, as judges need to be able to determine the gymnast is of good health and maintaining healthy circulation in their body to participate.\", \"from\": 2602, \"to\": 2773, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good reason\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2628}, {\"ngram\": \"judges\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2648}, {\"ngram\": \"the gymnast\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2689}, {\"ngram\": \"good health\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2707}, {\"ngram\": \"healthy circulation\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2743}, {\"ngram\": \"their body\", \"from\": 2747, \"to\": 2757}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nail colour is one of several indicators to pass the check, so if athletes do want to apply nail varnish, it must be a neutral colour.\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2909, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nail colour\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2786}, {\"ngram\": \"several indicators\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2815}, {\"ngram\": \"the check\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2833}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2849}, {\"ngram\": \"nail varnish\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"a neutral colour\", \"from\": 2892, \"to\": 2908}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did you know that swimmers have to manually submit their world record times to be approved by the sport's governing body?\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 2939}, {\"ngram\": \"their world\", \"from\": 2964, \"to\": 2975}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport's governing body\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's right.\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3048, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World Aquatics, formerly known as FINA, manually receive the time and only accept submissions by fax.\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.977133680817921e-38, \"text\": \"FINA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3063}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 3106, \"to\": 3114}, {\"ngram\": \"submissions\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3142}, {\"ngram\": \"fax\", \"from\": 3146, \"to\": 3149}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's unlikely to be much of an issue in Paris, though.\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3194, \"end\": 3199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.3699317295525638e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an issue\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only one new world record has been set in the swimming, with La Defense Arena's shallow pool - which is 0.85m shorter than the ones at Tokyo and Rio - blamed for the slower swimming times.\", \"from\": 3209, \"to\": 3397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3270, \"end\": 3280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Defense\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\"}, {\"begin\": 3344, \"end\": 3349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9993946672167413, \"rank\": 0.000605674186589035, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Only one new world record\", \"from\": 3209, \"to\": 3234}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming\", \"from\": 3251, \"to\": 3263}, {\"ngram\": \"the ones\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3340}, {\"ngram\": \"the slower swimming times\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3396}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us hope somebody told China's Pan Zhanle, who set the new 100m freestyle world record with a time of 46.40, to dust off his fax machine.\", \"from\": 3399, \"to\": 3539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3425, \"end\": 3430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999830014552153, \"rank\": 1.4633465853472441e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3405}, {\"ngram\": \"somebody\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3419}, {\"ngram\": \"the new 100m freestyle world record\", \"from\": 3453, \"to\": 3488}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3500}, {\"ngram\": \"his fax machine\", \"from\": 3523, \"to\": 3538}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the clippers out.\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3564, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the clippers\", \"from\": 3547, \"to\": 3559}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to rules in the lesser-seen water polo event, players are not allowed to have long nails as they can cause painful injuries underwater.\", \"from\": 3565, \"to\": 3710, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rules\", \"from\": 3578, \"to\": 3583}, {\"ngram\": \"the lesser-seen water polo event\", \"from\": 3587, \"to\": 3619}, {\"ngram\": \"players\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3628}, {\"ngram\": \"long nails\", \"from\": 3653, \"to\": 3663}, {\"ngram\": \"painful injuries\", \"from\": 3682, \"to\": 3698}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last year, an Australian player Tilly Kearns posted her battle scars from a match where an opponent's nails went unchecked, leaving her with a sore chest and several scratchmarks.\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3726, \"end\": 3736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.960010953217944, \"rank\": 0.04153767207465018, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 3750, \"end\": 3756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Kearns\", \"score\": 0.9997726516887053, \"rank\": 0.0002274000055542997, \"text\": \"Kearns\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Kearns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Kearns\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her battle scars\", \"from\": 3764, \"to\": 3780}, {\"ngram\": \"a match\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 3793}, {\"ngram\": \"an opponent's nails\", \"from\": 3800, \"to\": 3819}, {\"ngram\": \"a sore chest\", \"from\": 3853, \"to\": 3865}, {\"ngram\": \"several scratchmarks\", \"from\": 3870, \"to\": 3890}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And, if it wasn't already painstakingly obvious, players are strictly banned from grabbing other players in the groin area.\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 4016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"players\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 3949}, {\"ngram\": \"other players\", \"from\": 3984, \"to\": 3997}, {\"ngram\": \"the groin area\", \"from\": 4001, \"to\": 4015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we should not have to tell you that... Olympic wrestlers must carry a handkerchief, known as a \\\"bloodrag\\\", somewhere in their uniform when wrestling.\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4173, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic wrestlers\", \"from\": 4060, \"to\": 4077}, {\"ngram\": \"a handkerchief\", \"from\": 4089, \"to\": 4103}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"bloodrag\", \"from\": 4114, \"to\": 4125}, {\"ngram\": \"their uniform\", \"from\": 4141, \"to\": 4154}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 4175, \"to\": 4284, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your sign-up\", \"from\": 4182, \"to\": 4194}, {\"ngram\": \"content\", \"from\": 4206, \"to\": 4213}, {\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 4217, \"to\": 4221}, {\"ngram\": \"our understanding\", \"from\": 4259, \"to\": 4276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 4285, \"to\": 4361, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"adverts\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4309}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4315, \"to\": 4317}, {\"ngram\": \"3rd parties\", \"from\": 4322, \"to\": 4333}, {\"ngram\": \"our understanding\", \"from\": 4343, \"to\": 4360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 4362, \"to\": 4394, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any time\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy This is used to clear up any residual blood during a bout.\", \"from\": 4395, \"to\": 4477, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy Policy\", \"from\": 4400, \"to\": 4417}, {\"ngram\": \"any residual blood\", \"from\": 4443, \"to\": 4461}, {\"ngram\": \"a bout\", \"from\": 4469, \"to\": 4475}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While that's quite uncommon as it is not the same as boxing, the physical nature of wrestling can result in some blood being spilled.\", \"from\": 4478, \"to\": 4611, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the physical nature\", \"from\": 4539, \"to\": 4558}, {\"ngram\": \"wrestling\", \"from\": 4562, \"to\": 4571}, {\"ngram\": \"some blood\", \"from\": 4586, \"to\": 4596}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the event of bleeding, the wrestler will remove the cloth from their singlet and attempt to stop the bleeding or clean up any bodily fluids that may have gotten onto the mat.\", \"from\": 4613, \"to\": 4790, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 4616, \"to\": 4625}, {\"ngram\": \"bleeding\", \"from\": 4629, \"to\": 4637}, {\"ngram\": \"the wrestler\", \"from\": 4639, \"to\": 4651}, {\"ngram\": \"the cloth\", \"from\": 4664, \"to\": 4673}, {\"ngram\": \"thei